init_text:
Is It Selfish to Pursue Risky Sports Like Extreme Mountain Climbing?

Some sports, like extreme mountain climbing, are dangerous. Since there are varying degrees of risk in most, if not all, sports (such as the possibility of concussions, broken bones and even death), how does one decide where the line might be drawn between what is reasonable and what is not? Are some sports simply too dangerous to be called a sport?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is possible that they could end up leaving their family behind when they die on one of these daring adventures.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is very rare that these kinds of accidents happen, but they do happen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: While it is sometimes worth the risk to be happy, too much risk can come back to cause severe harm.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is the hard decision to make, but one that has to be made.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Extreme sports seem to be one of those.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As much as a person does not want to admit this fact, their family might be the thing that makes sure they are always careful and never crossing any

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I know that there are times when we can think of the thrill we feel on a mountain top or the one that is felt while doing a certain sport

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The trouble is that these sensations are so controlled by adrenaline and endorphins that it is only a fleeting feeling.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Eventually, the feelings of wanting that rush will outweigh the need for family and a feeling of being at home.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As a person's desire to pursue this thrill increases, their need for family decreases.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A person might not even have to make that decision but it would be good for them to know what might happen if their focus does change.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is a reminder for people to always have time for the family and not to focus all of their time on work or hobbies which eventually become so important
